.SH "NAME"
wimax_rfkill \- Set the software RF switch state for a WiMAX device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ wimax_rfkill('u
.BI "int wimax_rfkill(struct\ wimax_dev\ *\ " "wimax_dev" ", enum\ wimax_rf_state\ " "state" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIwimax_dev\fR
.RS 4
WiMAX device descriptor
.RE
.PP
\fIstate\fR
.RS 4
New RF state\&.
.RE
.SH "RETURN"
.PP
.PP
>= 0 toggle state if ok, < 0 errno code on error\&. The toggle state is returned as a bitmap, bit 0 being the hardware RF state, bit 1 the software RF state\&.
.PP
0 means disabled (\fBWIMAX_RF_ON\fR, radio on), 1 means enabled radio off (\fBWIMAX_RF_OFF\fR)\&.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.PP
Called by the user when he wants to request the WiMAX radio to be switched on (\fBWIMAX_RF_ON\fR) or off (\fBWIMAX_RF_OFF\fR)\&. With
\fBWIMAX_RF_QUERY\fR, just the current state is returned\&.
.SH "NOTE"
.PP
.PP
This call will block until the operation is complete\&.
